1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:01,540
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,540 --> 00:00:03,410
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,410 --> 00:00:05,210
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:07,910 --> 00:00:09,350
(Episode 52)

5
00:00:39,540 --> 00:00:40,550
It's okay.

6
00:00:42,980 --> 00:00:43,980
Everything's okay now.

7
00:00:48,350 --> 00:00:49,420
Min Jun.

8
00:00:58,030 --> 00:00:59,260
This time,

9
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:01,970
I'm never going to lose you.

10
00:01:52,050 --> 00:01:53,120
Jin...

11
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,120
Jin Ju...

12
00:02:00,530 --> 00:02:01,530
Jin Ju.

13
00:02:04,060 --> 00:02:05,130
Jin Ju...

14
00:02:11,670 --> 00:02:12,670
Chloe!

15
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:18,680
Min Jun!

16
00:02:20,250 --> 00:02:21,310
No!

17
00:02:21,910 --> 00:02:26,180
Min Jun!

18
00:02:26,850 --> 00:02:31,520
Oh no, Min Jun!

19
00:02:32,460 --> 00:02:34,730
Oh no. This can't be happening.

20
00:02:34,990 --> 00:02:38,830
No, Min Jun, no!

21
00:02:39,330 --> 00:02:41,230
This can't be. No!

22
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:42,870
Min Jun!

23
00:02:43,670 --> 00:02:47,370
Min Jun!

24
00:02:52,740 --> 00:02:54,410
Min... Min Jun.

25
00:02:58,780 --> 00:03:00,390
Oh no!

26
00:03:01,790 --> 00:03:03,960
No!

27
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,490
- Ambulance!
- Oh no.

28
00:03:05,490 --> 00:03:08,390
Call an ambulance, you idiots!

29
00:03:08,390 --> 00:03:12,300
Hurry up, you punks.
Call an ambulance!

30
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,030
Min Jun!

31
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,100
Min Jun, no!

32
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,260
Jung Ran, where are you?

33
00:03:48,930 --> 00:03:52,040
I went to the spa
like you told me to.

34
00:03:52,740 --> 00:03:54,140
Where'd you run off to?

35
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:55,770
None of your business.

36
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:59,410
You did exactly as I said
at the spa, right?

37
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:00,710
Yes.

38
00:04:01,050 --> 00:04:04,820
I had someone go in your place
and get the treatment.

39
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:09,290
The attendant said it was all set
and took care of everything.

40
00:04:10,460 --> 00:04:14,160
Just because President Kim
is watching you,

41
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,860
do we have to go through
all this trouble?

42
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:18,760
What are you up to,

43
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:21,470
trying to stay out of her sight?

44
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:25,470
Stop asking.

45
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:29,710
I went to the spa
and turned in early today.

46
00:04:30,740 --> 00:04:31,740
Stick to that.

47
00:04:31,910 --> 00:04:32,940
What?

48
00:04:34,180 --> 00:04:37,320
I'm not a very convincing liar.

49
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:40,350
Jung Ran, I... Jung Ran?

50
00:04:40,420 --> 00:04:43,120
Man, what a temper.

51
00:04:49,530 --> 00:04:51,200
Thanks to Park Tae Ho,

52
00:04:51,730 --> 00:04:54,900
I don't have to worry
about the security cameras,

53
00:04:55,830 --> 00:04:57,340
and I have a perfect alibi.

54
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,540
Get your hands off me.

55
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:06,540
Get your murderous hands off me.

56
00:05:06,980 --> 00:05:08,350
You don't...

57
00:05:12,550 --> 00:05:13,820
have a son anymore.

58
00:05:16,150 --> 00:05:18,360
Now, all I need is
for Park Min Jun to die.

59
00:05:20,830 --> 00:05:21,960
Kim Myung Hui.

60
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:26,030
See how it feels to lose your son.

61
00:05:30,670 --> 00:05:35,510
Min Jun! Min Jun, no.
Min Jun, stay with me!

62
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:36,870
Min Jun!

63
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:39,880
Him to the OR and her to the ER.

64
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:46,450
Hurry up! Faster!

65
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:56,030
Min Jun!

66
00:05:56,030 --> 00:05:58,000
You'll have to wait out here.

67
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:02,070
Hey. I'm Park Tae Ho of Adele!

68
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,870
Get all the doctors in this hospital
down here.

69
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:08,710
Tell them they'd better save my son!

70
00:06:08,770 --> 00:06:10,840
Please be patient.
We'll do everything we can.

71
00:06:11,140 --> 00:06:13,750
- Darn it. Hey!
- Min Jun!

72
00:06:15,150 --> 00:06:17,780
Good grief.
Myung Hui, come sit down.

73
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,290
What about the car that got away?

74
00:06:23,390 --> 00:06:24,390
Well...

75
00:06:24,860 --> 00:06:26,320
We haven't been able to find it.

76
00:06:26,790 --> 00:06:30,500
The CCTV cameras near the warehouse
were disabled ahead of time.

77
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:33,930
- I'm sorry, sir.
- Call my police contacts.

78
00:06:34,530 --> 00:06:39,070
Tell them to catch the punk
who did this to my son!

79
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:40,400
Yes, sir.

80
00:06:49,780 --> 00:06:51,780
Yes, I understand.

81
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,350
Mr. Hyun Jun.

82
00:06:55,990 --> 00:06:58,060
You need to go to the hospital.

83
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:00,460
Why the hospital?

84
00:07:00,890 --> 00:07:02,030
Is someone sick?

85
00:07:02,290 --> 00:07:05,900
Mr. Min Jun and Chloe were hit
by a car.

86
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:09,370
Min Jun and Chloe?

87
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,440
How bad is it? How are they doing?

88
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:13,600
Are they dead?

89
00:07:14,210 --> 00:07:18,110
What? Min Jun and Chloe were hit
by a car?

90
00:07:18,310 --> 00:07:20,310
Which hospital is it?

91
00:07:21,050 --> 00:07:22,280
Hanguk University Hospital.

92
00:07:28,420 --> 00:07:32,020
So, how are they?
Are they dead or alive?

93
00:07:32,460 --> 00:07:34,530
Chloe is being treated,

94
00:07:34,790 --> 00:07:37,430
and Mr. Min Jun is
in surgery right now.

95
00:07:37,530 --> 00:07:38,530
In surgery?

96
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:41,000
So he's not dead yet?

97
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:45,640
It almost sounds like
you were hoping he'd die.

98
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:51,810
Mrs. Ok, why would you twist
my words like that?

99
00:07:52,140 --> 00:07:55,380
I could've meant,
"Thank goodness he's not dead."

100
00:07:56,650 --> 00:07:57,750
Is that so?

101
00:07:59,150 --> 00:08:01,850
Wait a minute.
I need to talk to you.

102
00:08:12,460 --> 00:08:13,460
Jung Ran.

103
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,530
It wasn't you, was it?

104
00:08:17,570 --> 00:08:21,110
You didn't do this
to Min Jun and Chloe, did you?

105
00:08:22,470 --> 00:08:23,880
Is that why you asked me...

106
00:08:24,540 --> 00:08:26,840
to do that weird favor at the spa?

107
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:30,010
Please say I'm wrong.

108
00:08:32,580 --> 00:08:34,520
Why aren't you answering me?

109
00:08:35,420 --> 00:08:36,990
Kim Myung Hui started it.

110
00:08:38,090 --> 00:08:39,820
She exposed my past...

111
00:08:40,690 --> 00:08:42,190
and made me out to be a murderer.

112
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,000
Jung Ran!

113
00:08:44,430 --> 00:08:47,200
Do you have any idea
how Hyun Jun looks at me?

114
00:08:49,930 --> 00:08:52,170
He's ashamed to have me
as his mother.

115
00:08:54,070 --> 00:08:55,540
He even told me...

116
00:08:56,270 --> 00:08:58,080
to consider him dead.

117
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:02,280
Hyun Jun found out?

118
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:07,520
There's no going back
for me or for him.

119
00:09:08,420 --> 00:09:11,860
It's just like he said.
I've already lost my only son!

120
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:17,360
So it's only fair that Kim Myung Hui
loses her precious son too, right?

121
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:19,600
What do you think made Hyun Jun
turn out this way?

122
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:22,700
It's because you murdered someone!

123
00:09:23,330 --> 00:09:24,840
And now you're going to do it again?

124
00:09:25,540 --> 00:09:28,940
To Park Min Jun, of all people.
And Chloe, too!

125
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:35,780
What will you do
if Hyun Jun finds out?

126
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:37,750
This is not the way!

127
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:42,020
It won't matter if he never knows.

128
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:45,360
I won't get caught this time.

129
00:09:46,420 --> 00:09:47,430
How?

130
00:09:49,730 --> 00:09:53,230
Kim Myung Hui is one thing,
but Park Min Jun and Chloe...

131
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:56,200
Hyun Jun is better off
without them in his life.

132
00:09:57,770 --> 00:09:59,540
They're the reason
my son feels small...

133
00:09:59,540 --> 00:10:01,540
and constantly has to walk
on eggshells.

134
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:03,710
Once they're gone,

135
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:06,110
my Hyun Jun...

136
00:10:06,710 --> 00:10:08,750
can finally
hold his head up high again.

137
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,580
This isn't the way.

138
00:10:13,950 --> 00:10:16,420
You can't do this.

139
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,520
So?

140
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:22,630
What are you going to do
about it now?

141
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:26,130
Are you going to tell Park Tae Ho
and Hyun Jun everything?

142
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:30,530
You'll keep your mouth shut anyway,
so spare me the lecture.

143
00:10:31,270 --> 00:10:33,540
Just get your story straight
about me being at the spa.

144
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:35,570
Got it?

145
00:10:36,910 --> 00:10:38,880
And go find out if Park Min Jun...

146
00:10:39,540 --> 00:10:41,080
is dead or not.

147
00:10:51,090 --> 00:10:55,860
Doctor, how's Min Jun?
The surgery went well, didn't it?

148
00:10:56,490 --> 00:11:00,830
We did our best, but I can't promise
he'll regain consciousness.

149
00:11:01,430 --> 00:11:02,430
What?

150
00:11:02,970 --> 00:11:04,870
What do you mean
you can't guarantee it?

151
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:08,270
How can you call yourself a doctor
and say something...

152
00:11:08,770 --> 00:11:09,840
that irresponsible?

153
00:11:10,010 --> 00:11:13,140
He has severe brain swelling
caused by a traumatic brain injury.

154
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:14,580
For now, all we can do...

155
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,910
is reduce the pressure and wait.

156
00:11:18,450 --> 00:11:21,590
Call the hospital director
right now...

157
00:11:21,990 --> 00:11:22,990
and get him here.

158
00:11:22,990 --> 00:11:27,290
I want every doctor in this hospital
working on saving my son!

159
00:11:29,530 --> 00:11:30,590
Min Jun...

160
00:11:42,970 --> 00:11:44,740
- Where's Chloe?
- Excuse me?

161
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:47,910
Chloe.

162
00:11:48,850 --> 00:11:49,850
Chloe!

163
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:53,420
Chloe.

164
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,520
Chloe...

165
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:01,060
Mr. Park.

166
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:05,130
Is Chloe all right?

167
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:07,260
Thankfully,
she's not in critical condition.

168
00:12:07,970 --> 00:12:09,400
She hit her head in the accident,

169
00:12:09,830 --> 00:12:12,000
so they said it might be a while
before she wakes up.

170
00:12:13,070 --> 00:12:14,410
That's a relief.

171
00:12:19,010 --> 00:12:20,010
Chloe.

172
00:12:27,890 --> 00:12:31,390
Well, they'll be moving Chloe
to a regular room soon.

173
00:12:31,390 --> 00:12:34,260
You should go see Director Park now.

174
00:12:36,890 --> 00:12:40,360
Is Min Jun seriously hurt?

175
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:44,770
I heard he got hurt much worse
trying to save Chloe.

176
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:47,000
Go check on him yourself.

177
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,710
While saving Chloe?

178
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:50,440
Go on.

179
00:13:09,030 --> 00:13:10,260
Min Jun.

180
00:13:12,430 --> 00:13:14,200
Mom's right here.

181
00:13:17,570 --> 00:13:19,640
You won't give up, will you?

182
00:13:22,340 --> 00:13:23,940
You'll fight through this...

183
00:13:25,540 --> 00:13:27,440
and wake up for me, won't you?

184
00:13:41,590 --> 00:13:42,730
Min Jun.

185
00:13:50,430 --> 00:13:53,170
What on earth happened
at the warehouse?

186
00:13:54,070 --> 00:13:56,240
You, Chloe, and Min Jun.

187
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:58,340
Why were you all there?

188
00:14:00,180 --> 00:14:01,350
I was talking to Chloe...

189
00:14:02,050 --> 00:14:03,210
about work,

190
00:14:04,650 --> 00:14:06,050
that's all.

191
00:14:07,650 --> 00:14:11,720
But I have no idea
why Min Jun showed up there.

192
00:14:13,220 --> 00:14:16,530
I've got my police contacts
looking into it,

193
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:17,800
so hang tight.

194
00:14:19,060 --> 00:14:22,070
I'm going to find the driver
who did this to my son,

195
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:25,070
and I'll make them pay.

196
00:14:29,870 --> 00:14:30,940
Min Jun...

197
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,080
Min Jun.

198
00:14:43,190 --> 00:14:44,190
Choi Yu Na.

199
00:14:45,290 --> 00:14:46,460
How's Min Jun?

200
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:49,290
What about his surgery?
Did it go well?

201
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:52,400
Did you come after hearing the news?

202
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,430
Or were you there when it happened?

203
00:14:55,170 --> 00:14:57,870
I heard he got hurt
trying to save Chloe.

204
00:14:59,140 --> 00:15:01,570
Where and how did the accident
even happen?

205
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:02,840
I don't know.

206
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:05,340
I don't know anything.

207
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,850
I just did what I was told.

208
00:15:11,150 --> 00:15:12,520
It wasn't my fault.

209
00:15:13,450 --> 00:15:14,820
Chloe's to blame for everything.

210
00:15:16,350 --> 00:15:17,860
What did she do?

211
00:15:34,940 --> 00:15:37,210
My Hyun Jun is the only one
who got hurt.

212
00:15:37,810 --> 00:15:39,610
No matter what it takes,

213
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:43,080
I'll make you pay
for what you did to him.

214
00:15:44,010 --> 00:15:45,020
Because...

215
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:47,480
there are things only I can do.

216
00:15:47,850 --> 00:15:49,220
Just you wait.

217
00:15:49,450 --> 00:15:51,920
For everything you took from me,

218
00:15:53,060 --> 00:15:56,790
I've decided
to take the same from you.

219
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:00,360
Where's your mother?

220
00:16:01,730 --> 00:16:04,000
She was shocked
when she heard the news.

221
00:16:04,470 --> 00:16:05,700
I came in her stead.

222
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:07,440
She heard about it?

223
00:16:08,610 --> 00:16:12,540
Yes, Mrs. Ok told us,
and I came straight here.

224
00:16:14,810 --> 00:16:18,780
Head to the Adele warehouse.
Please, hurry.

225
00:16:29,230 --> 00:16:31,700
Mrs. Ok, please tell me.

226
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:34,400
Why did you call me and say that?

227
00:16:34,530 --> 00:16:37,470
Oh Jung Ran.
She's behind this, isn't she?

228
00:16:37,940 --> 00:16:40,340
Please, just be honest
and tell me what you know.

229
00:16:41,210 --> 00:16:45,680
I only saw Mr. Min Jun leaving
in a rush.

230
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:47,340
As he rushed out,

231
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:50,580
he said there was danger
at the warehouse and he had to go.

232
00:16:51,250 --> 00:16:55,250
Wait, are you saying this has
nothing to do with Oh Jung Ran?

233
00:16:56,620 --> 00:16:59,420
I'm not entirely sure about that.

234
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:01,190
When Mr. Min Jun wakes up,

235
00:17:01,190 --> 00:17:04,760
you can ask him
what happened yourselves.

236
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:07,700
No, that can't be right.

237
00:17:08,370 --> 00:17:10,530
This is definitely
Oh Jung Ran's doing.

238
00:17:12,670 --> 00:17:13,670
Darn it.

239
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:26,880
Oh Jung Ran!

240
00:17:30,620 --> 00:17:32,760
Why are you yelling
in the middle of the night?

241
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:34,660
It was you, wasn't it?

242
00:17:34,990 --> 00:17:36,130
What do you mean?

243
00:17:36,590 --> 00:17:41,100
You tried to kill Min Jun
by running him over, didn't you?

244
00:17:42,670 --> 00:17:46,100
Oh Jung Ran, you!
You'd better start talking.

245
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:48,240
Did you do this to my son?

246
00:17:50,010 --> 00:17:51,140
Come on!

247
00:17:51,380 --> 00:17:53,810
Why do I get blamed
for every accident?

248
00:17:55,050 --> 00:17:57,250
No matter how furious I was,

249
00:17:57,250 --> 00:17:59,450
I could never hurt your son.

250
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:01,150
Am I that stupid?

251
00:18:01,590 --> 00:18:02,950
Stop lying.

252
00:18:03,150 --> 00:18:05,760
You're the one
who sent Min Jun to that warehouse.

253
00:18:06,190 --> 00:18:08,690
It's remote, the perfect place
to stage an accident.

254
00:18:09,030 --> 00:18:11,400
You thought you could pull it off
without leaving any evidence.

255
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:12,600
No.

256
00:18:12,930 --> 00:18:16,070
It looks to me like you're the one
taking advantage of the situation.

257
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:20,340
You're trying to use
your son's accident to frame me.

258
00:18:21,470 --> 00:18:25,780
Honey, I was at the spa
getting a massage all evening.

259
00:18:25,980 --> 00:18:29,380
She's seizing the opportunity
to pin this on me!

260
00:18:32,550 --> 00:18:35,420
If you don't believe me,
call my driver and ask him.

261
00:18:35,420 --> 00:18:36,420
No.

262
00:18:36,920 --> 00:18:39,190
I'll check your alibi myself.

263
00:18:39,490 --> 00:18:42,430
I'll even review
the security footage at the spa!

264
00:18:44,390 --> 00:18:45,730
Please help me, sir.

265
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:49,130
Please find out
if she hired someone to do this.

266
00:18:50,470 --> 00:18:53,000
What's to stop you
from fabricating evidence?

267
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:57,440
Honey, look into this yourself
instead of taking her word for it,

268
00:18:57,610 --> 00:18:59,640
and prove my innocence.

269
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:01,880
Your innocence?

270
00:19:03,380 --> 00:19:04,480
If you...

271
00:19:05,180 --> 00:19:07,350
were the one who targeted Min Jun,

272
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:10,190
you'd better be ready
for what's coming.

273
00:19:11,490 --> 00:19:12,960
Because I will make you pay back...

274
00:19:13,490 --> 00:19:15,860
in the most painful
and agonizing way.

275
00:19:17,390 --> 00:19:19,060
Goodness.

276
00:19:27,470 --> 00:19:28,470
Are you sure...

277
00:19:29,670 --> 00:19:30,970
it wasn't you?

278
00:19:32,610 --> 00:19:36,010
I said, if you don't believe me,
investigate it yourself.

279
00:19:36,210 --> 00:19:39,520
You should trust the evidence,
not Kim Myung Hui's words.

280
00:19:39,980 --> 00:19:41,050
Right?

281
00:19:52,100 --> 00:19:54,730
How did Min Jun and Chloe end up
in that accident together?

282
00:19:54,730 --> 00:19:56,170
What was that car about?

283
00:19:56,170 --> 00:19:57,940
It didn't seem
like Chairman Park knew either.

284
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,240
No, wait.

285
00:20:00,740 --> 00:20:02,710
He could just be playing dumb.

286
00:20:04,840 --> 00:20:07,810
What if he set it up
in case Chloe tried to run away?

287
00:20:09,450 --> 00:20:10,450
Or...

288
00:20:12,380 --> 00:20:14,150
was I a target too?

289
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:19,790
What's going to happen to Min Jun?

290
00:20:20,460 --> 00:20:22,260
And what's going to happen to me?

291
00:20:33,170 --> 00:20:34,610
- Oh, dear.
- My gosh.

292
00:20:36,810 --> 00:20:39,980
Do you think Yu Na will be okay?

293
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:43,810
She said the accident happened
right in front of her.

294
00:20:43,950 --> 00:20:46,820
She came in pale as a ghost.

295
00:20:48,090 --> 00:20:50,150
How on earth could
something like that happen?

296
00:20:51,860 --> 00:20:53,660
It's karma.

297
00:20:53,860 --> 00:20:56,990
Remember how disrespectfully
that family treated us?

298
00:20:57,260 --> 00:21:01,230
It's karma, plain and simple.
You reap what you sow.

299
00:21:02,330 --> 00:21:06,740
That's a pretty harsh thing to say
when someone got hurt.

300
00:21:07,540 --> 00:21:09,270
You know how that old song goes.

301
00:21:09,510 --> 00:21:12,780
<i>The one who abandons me</i>

302
00:21:12,840 --> 00:21:16,550
<i>Won't get very far before they fall</i>

303
00:21:17,450 --> 00:21:22,150
That jerk who dumped our Yu Na
totally deserved to get hurt.

304
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:25,690
You're so cold-hearted.

305
00:21:26,260 --> 00:21:28,490
What? As if.

306
00:21:31,330 --> 00:21:32,460
He totally had it coming.

307
00:21:38,940 --> 00:21:42,210
The doctor said you'd wake up soon,

308
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:44,810
so why are you sleeping for so long?

309
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:50,910
Are you catching up on sleep
because you've been through so much?

310
00:21:51,650 --> 00:21:55,090
Is it because you'd feel guilty
waking up before Min Jun does?

311
00:21:57,620 --> 00:21:58,720
Please, wake up.

312
00:21:59,760 --> 00:22:02,860
You should wake up first
and then help him wake up too.

313
00:22:14,540 --> 00:22:16,210
What brings you here
so early in the morning?

314
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,880
I was worried about Chloe.

315
00:22:20,180 --> 00:22:21,750
Hasn't she woken up yet?

316
00:22:26,450 --> 00:22:28,990
I'm sorry, but I'm going to have
to ask you to leave.

317
00:22:29,520 --> 00:22:30,520
Excuse me?

318
00:22:31,660 --> 00:22:32,990
I made it very clear...

319
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:36,160
that I didn't approve of you,
Mr. Park.

320
00:22:36,490 --> 00:22:39,760
Chloe was with Chairman Park
and Choi Yu Na at the Adele warehouse...

321
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:41,360
when the accident happened.

322
00:22:42,470 --> 00:22:44,230
Until we know exactly what happened,

323
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:48,270
I don't want anyone from Adele here,
so please leave.

324
00:22:49,370 --> 00:22:52,340
- Father.
- I said get out. Leave!

325
00:22:52,740 --> 00:22:54,710
Father, wait. Hold on.

326
00:23:35,650 --> 00:23:36,790
What did you find out?

327
00:23:37,320 --> 00:23:38,990
Did you check
the spa's CCTV footage?

328
00:23:39,190 --> 00:23:41,530
Oh Jung Ran was lying, wasn't she?

329
00:23:43,490 --> 00:23:46,830
Oh Jung Ran really was at the spa...

330
00:23:47,230 --> 00:23:48,400
when Min Jun got run over.

331
00:23:50,030 --> 00:23:51,100
That's impossible.

332
00:24:01,580 --> 00:24:02,580
It can't be.

333
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:06,450
It has to be doctored.
That could be someone else.

334
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:08,690
I even checked with the staff there.

335
00:24:09,220 --> 00:24:10,490
Oh Jung Ran was there.

336
00:24:11,290 --> 00:24:14,960
She even got the staff involved.
I'll verify it myself.

337
00:24:16,060 --> 00:24:17,860
At this rate,
you're going to collapse.

338
00:24:18,630 --> 00:24:21,330
Woo Jin and I will
keep looking into it,

339
00:24:21,530 --> 00:24:23,700
so please try to stay calm and wait.

340
00:24:32,910 --> 00:24:36,080
Ma'am, the police are here.

341
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:46,960
The car!

342
00:24:47,090 --> 00:24:49,290
Did you find the car
that hit Min Jun?

343
00:24:49,990 --> 00:24:52,660
We didn't find any useful evidence
at the scene.

344
00:24:53,500 --> 00:24:56,600
It's a secluded area,
so there's no traffic footage,

345
00:24:57,170 --> 00:25:01,400
and the warehouse's internal cameras
don't cover the accident area.

346
00:25:02,110 --> 00:25:03,210
In other words,

347
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:06,980
it's the perfect place to commit a crime
without leaving a trace.

348
00:25:18,590 --> 00:25:19,590
That's right.

349
00:25:19,920 --> 00:25:22,990
It's the place Park Tae Ho set up
to get rid of Chloe.

350
00:25:23,890 --> 00:25:27,530
He would've made sure
nothing could catch him in the act.

351
00:25:30,070 --> 00:25:33,540
The plan I set up
to quietly get rid of Chloe...

352
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:37,240
ended up hurting my own son...

353
00:25:37,940 --> 00:25:39,840
and coming back
to bite me like this.

354
00:25:41,710 --> 00:25:44,680
So, because there's no evidence,

355
00:25:45,050 --> 00:25:47,080
you can't do anything?

356
00:25:47,350 --> 00:25:49,250
You can at least look for witnesses.

357
00:25:49,350 --> 00:25:50,720
We haven't found any witnesses,

358
00:25:50,890 --> 00:25:54,520
but we got a lead
from a dashcam nearby.

359
00:25:55,930 --> 00:25:57,660
A lead? What kind of lead?

360
00:25:58,530 --> 00:26:00,400
Will it help you catch
the person responsible?

361
00:26:27,390 --> 00:26:30,290
What did you find
on the dashcam footage?

362
00:26:30,660 --> 00:26:32,300
Did it capture the license plate?

363
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:33,500
The license plate was...

364
00:26:36,370 --> 00:26:37,700
The vehicle didn't have one.

365
00:26:39,140 --> 00:26:42,570
What? Are you kidding me right now?

366
00:26:43,310 --> 00:26:44,740
How is that supposed to be a lead?

367
00:26:47,310 --> 00:26:51,180
If they removed the license plate
beforehand...

368
00:26:51,610 --> 00:26:54,250
Yes. It could be a hit-and-run,

369
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:56,850
but there's a chance
this was premeditated.

370
00:26:59,390 --> 00:27:02,330
Are you saying
someone deliberately...

371
00:27:03,260 --> 00:27:04,830
targeted my son?

372
00:27:05,860 --> 00:27:07,830
We believe Chloe
may have been a target too.

373
00:27:08,900 --> 00:27:11,130
Wait, Chloe?

374
00:27:11,500 --> 00:27:14,870
It's possible
she was the intended target.

375
00:27:16,070 --> 00:27:17,070
Right.

376
00:27:17,510 --> 00:27:19,940
Didn't you say Min Jun got hurt
trying to save her?

377
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:23,810
That means Chloe may have been
the real target, not Min Jun.

378
00:27:24,310 --> 00:27:28,890
That's right. Once Chloe wakes up,
we'll investigate further.

379
00:27:30,320 --> 00:27:32,090
Now that we've filled you in
on the investigation,

380
00:27:32,460 --> 00:27:33,620
we'll be on our way.

381
00:27:34,590 --> 00:27:35,590
Let's go.

382
00:27:42,830 --> 00:27:44,030
See?

383
00:27:44,230 --> 00:27:46,600
The police haven't found
a single piece of evidence,

384
00:27:46,670 --> 00:27:49,040
and I have a solid alibi
for being at the spa.

385
00:27:50,270 --> 00:27:53,280
Don't go accusing innocent people,
you hear me?

386
00:28:04,850 --> 00:28:06,690
When Chloe wakes up,

387
00:28:07,290 --> 00:28:09,890
they'll investigate further?

388
00:28:16,530 --> 00:28:17,570
I'm good.

389
00:28:18,440 --> 00:28:21,400
They can say it was premeditated,
but there's no proof.

390
00:28:32,220 --> 00:28:34,450
What are you doing? Are you insane?

391
00:28:34,620 --> 00:28:37,220
That's right. I've lost it.

392
00:28:37,890 --> 00:28:40,720
How could I be in my right mind
when my son is fighting for his life?

393
00:28:41,830 --> 00:28:44,730
The woman who tried to hurt my son
is right here,

394
00:28:44,730 --> 00:28:46,230
but I can't even kill her!

395
00:28:47,900 --> 00:28:51,200
So how do you expect me
not to lose my mind?

396
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:54,940
I have to admit,

397
00:28:55,870 --> 00:28:59,310
seeing you lose it
is pretty satisfying.

398
00:29:01,040 --> 00:29:02,050
What?

399
00:29:02,110 --> 00:29:05,780
It's about time you knew the pain
of losing your only child.

400
00:29:06,580 --> 00:29:09,190
It feels like your guts are being
ripped out, doesn't it?

401
00:29:09,520 --> 00:29:12,220
Aren't you so torn up you feel like
you're losing your mind?

402
00:29:14,160 --> 00:29:16,030
Seeing this look on your face...

403
00:29:16,460 --> 00:29:17,790
actually makes me feel better.

404
00:29:23,330 --> 00:29:24,800
The face of a grieving mother?

405
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:28,870
If that's what you want to see,
I'll show you.

406
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:33,810
Go on. Look at my face.
Take a good, long look!

407
00:29:34,110 --> 00:29:35,180
Go ahead!

408
00:29:35,250 --> 00:29:38,980
- Just die!
- No...

409
00:29:41,750 --> 00:29:43,390
Ms. Kim, stop. That's enough!

410
00:29:43,390 --> 00:29:45,390
- Please stop!
- Die!

411
00:29:45,860 --> 00:29:47,220
- Let go of me!
- Please!

412
00:29:47,220 --> 00:29:48,320
Let go!

413
00:29:48,320 --> 00:29:51,030
Please get it together.
Director Park's awake.

414
00:29:54,260 --> 00:29:56,900
Min Jun... Is he really?

415
00:29:59,440 --> 00:30:02,240
Ma'am, wait for me. Ma'am!

416
00:30:04,740 --> 00:30:06,110
Park Min Jun woke up?

417
00:30:07,440 --> 00:30:09,450
Why couldn't he just die?

418
00:30:10,110 --> 00:30:11,580
Why?

419
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:27,160
Min Jun.

420
00:30:31,770 --> 00:30:32,770
Mother.

421
00:30:34,470 --> 00:30:35,470
That's right.

422
00:30:37,310 --> 00:30:38,440
Yes, Min Jun.

423
00:30:40,340 --> 00:30:41,440
It's Mom.

424
00:30:47,950 --> 00:30:48,950
Thank you...

425
00:30:51,290 --> 00:30:52,360
for waking up.

426
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:54,990
Thank you so much.

427
00:31:52,980 --> 00:31:54,450
Who are you?

428
00:32:05,800 --> 00:32:06,800
Who are you?

429
00:32:38,900 --> 00:32:41,830
(Pearl in Red)

430
00:32:42,230 --> 00:32:46,340
My son is alive, but I can't
even see him or hold him.

431
00:32:46,740 --> 00:32:49,970
I should've made Kim Myung Hui
suffer this exact same pain.

432
00:32:50,370 --> 00:32:52,940
What happened at the warehouse
on the day of the accident?

433
00:32:53,010 --> 00:32:55,350
If you're curious, ask the chairman
instead of hounding me.

434
00:32:55,350 --> 00:32:56,680
- Hey.
- I have nothing to say,

435
00:32:56,680 --> 00:32:59,250
so keep your mouth shut
and don't say a word to the police.

436
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:01,250
Still no updates
on the hit-and-run driver?

437
00:33:01,250 --> 00:33:04,520
The investigation has stalled
because the victims have amnesia.

438
00:33:04,750 --> 00:33:07,420
Enough with the excuses.
Tell them to find him at all costs!

439
00:33:07,820 --> 00:33:10,030
The punk who hurt my son...

440
00:33:11,190 --> 00:33:13,060
will get no mercy from me.

441
00:33:13,630 --> 00:33:15,630
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
